documentation.text:
Return how much domains the Series has registered using this Registrar.
 @param addr The string containing the series address.

params.ensAddr: The address of the ENS registry.
params.node: The node that this registrar administers.
params.resolverAddr: The resolver where domains will use to register.

params.addr: The string containing the series address.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.label: The hash of the label to register.
params.owner: The address of the new owner(Series Manager).

params.target: Series contract that registry will point.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

ownedDomains(address).notice: Return how much domains the Series has registered using this Registrar.

register(bytes32,address,address).notice: Register a name, or change the owner of an existing registration.

registerAndStore(string,address,address).notice: Register a name, and store the domain to reverse lookup.

resolve(address,uint8).notice: Return some domain from a series. As a single series could claim multiple domains, the resolve function here has a index parameter to point a specific domain to be retrieved.
